ccupy rocky coasts from New England northward, and patchworks of forests and heathlands occur in eastern Canada and in the Appalachian highlands. While the study of alternative states in the marine system can be approached experimentally, the scale of disturbance required to switch forests to heathlands is too large for experimentation and must rely on the use of other approaches.},
